documentation.overview:
The material app bar supplies a titlebar and an icon menu button to the app. 

Make a proposed icon to be a component then select and swap it in the app bar component if you propose to replace current icon by the proposed icon.

interfaces.content: After the menu button has been tapped, the mesage `menu_tapped` is received from the app bar component.
After the icon 1 button has been tapped, the mesage `icon1_tapped` is received from the app bar component.
After the icon 2 button has been tapped, the mesage `icon2_tapped` is received from the app bar component.
After the icon 3 button has been tapped, the mesage `icon3_tapped` is received from the app bar component.

documentation.overview: The material text field supplies a field for text inputting.

interfaces.content: After the text field input box has been focused in, the message `input_focused_in` is received from the text field component.
After the text field input box has been focused out, the message `input_focused_out` is received from the text field component.
After return key has been pressed, the message `return_pressed_with_value` is received from the text field component, and the input text is received along with the message.
Send the message `input_focus_in` to the text field component when the text field input box needs to be focused in.
Send the message `input_focus_out` to the text field component when the text field input box needs to be focused out.
After text has been typed, the message `input_typed_with_value` is received from the text field component, and the input text is received along with the message.

documentation.overview: The material progress indicators, it shows loading progress with 0-100% in linear form.

interfaces.name: Duration
interfaces.content: Set the proposed duration for the progress, which indicates the time cost of 0-100%.
After the progress has been completed, the message `progress_completed` is received from the progress indicator component.
Send the message `progress_start` to the progress indicator component when the progress needs to be started.

documentation.overview: The material progress indicators for inderterminate loading duration.
The material checkbox can be checked for indicating an option is selected.

interfaces.content: After the checkbox has been checked, the message `checkbox_checked` is received from the checkbox component.
After the checkbox has been unchecked, the message `checkbox_unchecked` is received from the checkbox component.

documentation.overview:
The material radio button supplies a group of options for one option selecting. 

Put several radio buttons with different label name into a scene thus a radio group can be composed automatically. And further by setting `radioGroup` variable different radio group can be created.

interfaces.name: radioGroup
interfaces.content:
The variable for radio group setting.  

Set same `radioGroup` value to several radio button components thus a radio group can be composed.

Different radio groups in a scene can be separated by setting different `radioGroup` values for each group.

interfaces.name: defaultSelected
interfaces.content:
This indicates whether the radio button is selected in default.

When set to `true`, the radio button is selected initially on the scene.
After the radio button has been unselected, the message `radiobutton_unselected` is received from the radio button component.
After the radio button has been selected, the message `radiobutton_selected` is received from the radio button component.

documentation.overview: The material switch can be toggled on and toggled off.

interfaces.content: After the switch has been toggled on, the message `toggled_on` is received from the switch component.
After the switch has been toggled off, the message `toggled_off` is received from the switch component.

documentation.overview:
The slider can adjust a value within a certain range.  

The minimum / maximum / initial value of the slider can be set. The current value changes when the slider is dragged.

interfaces.name: minValue
interfaces.content: Set the minimum value for the slider.

interfaces.name: maxValue
interfaces.content: Set the maximum value for the slider.

interfaces.name: initialValue
interfaces.content: Set the initial value for the slider.

interfaces.name: roundUpNumber
interfaces.content:
This indicates whether current value includes a decimal point or not.
When set to  `true` , current value is an integer value that has been rounded up.
When set to  `false` , current value is a value with two decimal places.

Send the message `slider_change_with_value` to the slider component when the thumb image of the slider needs to be moved based on a certain value. 
A value can be sent along with the the message.

Every time the slider is dragged, the message `slider_changed_with_value` is received from the slider component.
The value, received along with the message, can be assigned to a variable.
